author: tellison
msg: Add two new private constructors to String that can be invoked by the JIT as optimizations when compiling string handling code,

e.g. Common expressions like  String s = s1 + s2;  generates something of the form  String s = new StringBuffer().append(s1).append(s2).toString(); but with the helpers it can be more efficiently represented as String s = new String(s1, s2);
